snippet.textDisplay:
uMm AcTuAlLy, It’S nOt ThE fOrTnItE dAnCe, It’S cAlLeD tHe FlOsS!¡ hE dId NoT dO tHe DeFaUlT dAnCe

Cringey jokes aside, I feel oddly fine with Sonic flossing. Weird things to say I know but I guess that’s the world we’re living in. For one, he only did it twice and it’s not like they took a break from the film to show him flossing like Shazam did. Speaking of Shazam, secondly, I think I’m mostly fine with this because in the context of the movie, Sonic’s still just a teenager. Yeah it may or may not be dated in a few years, but I don’t see any problem with it if it’s something minor. I mean after all, Avengers: Endgame had like a full minute scene of Korg playing Fortnite and suddenly that’s ok whereas Sonic does the floss and suddenly everyone loses their minds

snippet.textDisplay: Don't forget that the people that 'fixed' Sonic were all fired because Paramount and Disney (for Lion King) combined didn't pay them enough to stay open so the parent company closed them.  They have the opportunity to move to another location but they likely won't get anything extra for any bonuses sent to the company. Everyone seems to be on a tirade about seeing it because they finally listened to fans, but fail to look at the full picture: Paramount didn't redesign sonic, the Sonic Team didn't design the new sonic, in fact they both agreed to the ugly design; Sega's indie team at Sonic Mania provided the art and redesigns from their artist, MPC Vancouver remade all the scenes, and now fans are throwing money at a company that allowed 400 to 800 jobs be taken from the market.
snippet.textOriginal: Don't forget that the people that 'fixed' Sonic were all fired because Paramount and Disney (for Lion King) combined didn't pay them enough to stay open so the parent company closed them.  They have the opportunity to move to another location but they likely won't get anything extra for any bonuses sent to the company.
